won't know ahead of time how many args a function needs
python allows functions to collect arbitrary number of args from calling statments
* - asterick in parameter name tells python to make an empty tuple called toppings & pack
    whatever values it receives into this tuple

mixing positional & arbitray args
Want function to accept sveral diff kinds of arg, the parameter that accepts
    the arbitray of args must be placed last in fucntion def
    Python matchs positional & keywords args 1st and then collects remaining args in 
        final parameter

using arbitary keyword args
function accepts as many key-value pairs as the calling statement provides
